Bring 1 cup water and a pinch of @salt{pinch} to a boil in a #small pot{}. Once boiling, add @Basmati Rice{1/2%cup}, cover, and reduce to a simmer. Cook until tender, ~{15-20%minutes}. Remove from heat and keep covered.

Wash and dry all produce. Trim and halve @Green Beans{6%ounce}. Peel and mince @Ginger{1%thumb}. Mince or grate @Garlic{2%clove}. Trim @Scallions{2} and cut into 1-inch pieces. Core, seed, and thinly slice @Red Bell Pepper{1}. Pick leaves from @Mint{1/4%ounce} and coarsely chop.

Heat a large drizzle of @Vegetable Oil{4%teaspoon} in a #large pan{} over high heat. Add green beans, bell pepper, and scallions and toss until softened and starting to brown, ~{4-5%minutes}. Season with @salt{} and @Pepper{}. Remove from pan and set aside.

Reduce heat to medium and add a large drizzle of oil to same pan. Add garlic and ginger and toss until fragrant, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Increase heat to medium-high and add @Ground Pork{10%ounce}. Break up meat into pieces with #spatula{} or #wooden spoon{} and cook until browned and crisp at edges, ~{5-6%minutes}. Toss in veggies, @Soy Sauce{1%ounce}, and @Honey{1/2%ounce}. Season with salt and pepper.

Remove pan from heat and stir in half of the mint. Fluff rice with a #fork{}. Divide rice between plates and top with stir-fry. Garnish with remaining mint, if desired.